class_notes: As a Community Engaged Learning (CEL) course, students will partner with a particular community organization to serve for a total of 18 hours in addition to regularly scheduled class time.
course_description: The purpose of this course is to trace the cognitive, physical, and psychosocial changes of the human being from conception through adolescence and to examine the factors that influence this course of development.
